      <abstract>
        <p>We investigated 2 fatal cases of Rocky Mountain spotted fever that occurred in 2003 and 2004 near the same locality in Colombia where the disease was first reported in the 1930s. A retrospective serosurvey of febrile patients showed that &gt;21% of the serum samples had antibodies against spotted fever group rickettsiae.</p>
      </abstract>
